Bank Marketing Analysis ¶

The aim of this analysis is to delve into the insights hidden within the banking dataset and address the following research questions:¶

  • a) How do different client attributes, such as age, job type, marital status, and education, impact subscribing to a term deposit?
  • b) Are there any observable trends in client contact strategies, such as communication type, month of contact, and day of the week, that impact subscription rates?
  • c) What impact does the duration of contact have on the subscription decision?
  • d) How does the subscription rate differ between different job types, education levels, and marital statuses?

Presented by:¶

Mohamed Anwar ¶

Q15) Which communication way (cellular, telephone) have the highest subscription rates for term deposits?¶

In [24]:
subscription_rates = df.groupby('contact')['y'].value_counts(normalize=True)
cellular_rate = subscription_rates['cellular']['yes']
telephone_rate = subscription_rates['telephone']['yes']
print(f"Subscription rate for Cellular: {cellular_rate:.2%}")
print(f"Subscription rate for Telephone: {telephone_rate:.2%}")

Subscription rate for Cellular: 14.74%
Subscription rate for Telephone: 5.23%
